27/11/2005
PIESTANY, Slovakia -- Albania took over the rotating presidency of the Central European Initiative (CEI) for 2006, succeeding Slovakia.
The transfer took place Friday (25 November) at a ceremony during the two-day CEI summit in Piestany.
Albanian Prime Minister Sali Berisha said that the priorities of the Albanian presidency would be increased co-operation and communication, particularly in the areas of EU integration and the economy.
Also Friday, members of the European Parliament (EP) delegation wrapped up a two-day visit to Albania with a statement urging reform of the country's electoral process as well as settlement of property issues.
The delegation was in Tirana for the 12th Albania-EP inter-parliamentary meeting.
(Albanian News - 26/11/05;
Hina - 25/11/05)
